<item>
            <title>[SPARK-3456] YarnAllocator can lose container requests to RM</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-3456</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I haven&apos;t actually tested this yet, but I believe that spark on yarn can lose container requests to the RM.  The reason is that we ask for the total number upfront (say x) but then we don&apos;t ask for anymore unless some are missing and if we do then we could erase the original request.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ask for 3 containers&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 is allocated&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ask for 0 containers since asked for 3 originally (2 left)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the 1 allocated dies&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We now ask for 1 since its missing, this will override whatever is on the yarn side (in this case 2).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Then we lose the 2 more we need.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
